<br>
Hear me out before you fire away at me for defaming him, as I am well aware of the deserved esteem in which you hold him.<br>
<br>
I've spent a lot of time in groups with Trist and Maeve, known em for better'n a few years now, and Maeve near as long as I've played EQ (*waves* to Captain Looooove and the Holognome). We grouped quite a bit and Trist was even tossing around the idea of recruiting with a guild that I was an officer in (Moonlight Crusaders, and this might show how old a bit of history this is).<br>
<br>
There's a whole lot of people what say good things about Trist, and a whole lotta people what say bad things. Hard to reconcile the two at face value. The key to the matter is this...<br>
<br>
Tristadorn is very, VERY good at pissing people off.<br>
<br>
Tristadorn is a fiery, passionate fellow, and this is the characteristic that causes so many love/hate reactions. People that are on his good side see his passion as drive, fire, what have you. People on his bad side see him as an inrascible flamethrower with a penchant for nasty insults and pointed invective.<br>
<br>
I have been on both sides of Tristadorn these many years, and can safely make these observations. <br>
<br>
To those of you who think Radiant has a bad rep, I ask that you attempt to look at Radiant's actions outside of Tristadorn's posts. I do not defend them, merely point out that I see them being defamed far less than many.<br>
<br>
To those of you that think that Radiant shines like morning dew and fresh fallen snow, look to unmended fences and the smoldering ruin of bridges left burnt.<br>
<br>
Again, I reiterate the fact that, while our relationship is fairly cool due to some RL stupidity from years ago, I respect a lot of things that make up the man behind Tristadorn, and feel no shame in admitting it. Nothing but love for Maeve, and that helps too =)<br>
<br>
I am more on the side of those who think that Radiant has a rep more good than bad, especially since seeing Reahn's post on her decision. While I've never had the pleasure of grouping with Raehn, I have always been impressed with the tone of good humour I've seen, and am doubly impressed that you would step forward thus and extend the olive branch. Not that I am implying that you intended this effect, but Radiant certainly looks the better for your presence and your actions, Raehn.<br>
<br>
This is not a flame at Trist, more an honest opinion of one of the reasons why Radiant's rep does not always reflect its' actions. <p>a_Bearhat01<BR>
